This paper is about nitrogen-vacancy (NV) centers in diamond — specifically their excited-state electric dipole transitions. This is NOT about superconducting qubits, thin films, or any of the materials (Ta, Nb, Al, TiN, etc.) relevant to superconducting qubit research. The paper has no resonators, no Qi, no T1/T2 for superconducting qubits, no film deposition, and no junction fabrication.

The relevance to the superconducting qubit materials characterization database is essentially zero. There are no extractable fields from the schema that apply to this paper.

